Package edu.iit.ir.simpledm.gui Description

Provides classes for displaying the windows for SimpleDM.
In the main window, MenuFrame, there are four panels which are SettingPanel, PreprocessingPanel, ModelPanel, and Logger. Each panel will be activated step by step after a previous step is confirmed.

  • SettingPanel provides a service to open a file and display the types of attributes. A user can change the type of an attribute if the program incorrectly detected it. However, since the program accepts only 'ARFF' formatted file, which explicitly mentions the types and names of all attributes in a header, a user is not recommended to change the types.
  • PreprocessingPanel provides the options of preprocessing.
  • ModelPanel receives an input value for the N-folds cross validation. And a user can choose a model to build and test.
  • Logger panel displays the status of processing by writing an sentence with current time.
